The ban on fishing, commercial diving and other marine activities at Durban harbour has been lifted. The Transnet National Port Authority banned the activities in early May. DURBAN - The ban on fishing, commercial diving and other marine activities at Durban harbour has been provisionally lifted. The Transnet National Port Authority banned the activities in early May after sewage leaked into the harbour, from the eThekwini municipal sewerage system. A ban was put in place after sewage was found flowing into the harbour from the eTthekwini Municipality's reticulation system. READ:Â Marine life in jeopardy as sewage pours into Durban harbour Darryl Williams from the Point Yacht Club said the water quality has significantly improved but there is still work to be done. The ban has been provisionally lifted and Williams cautioned people to still exercise due caution when interacting with water from the harbour.